                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><persName>S. GERSTMAN &amp; CO.</persName>,</p>\n            <p>Commission Merchants</p>\n            <p>\n                <placeName>186 Congress &amp; 85 St. Julian Sts.</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><placeName>SAVANNAH, GA</placeName>.</p>\n            <p><persName role=\"author\">S. GERSTMAN</persName>. <persName>W. BARNETT</persName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Savannah</placeName>, <date>April 17 1866</date></p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">Dear Sir!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I have recd the<lb/> Tafelas &amp;c and have collected<lb/> all the\n                money except for<lb/> two which the party are not<lb/> in town but will be here<lb/>\n                in a few days, when I will<lb/> forward you a draft for<lb/> the full amount, I\n                would<lb/> advise you if possible to<lb/> come out to inaugurate the<lb/> B.B. Lodge\n                here as I am confident<lb/> that you could get over 50<lb/> subscribers for the\n                Occident<lb/> &amp; could sell over 100 copies<lb/> of your daily Prayers, and\n                probably</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rj49f69/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
